The  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  fell to the
lowest in three months, dropping 1.8 percent to 1,488.24 at the
2 p.m. close in Dubai. Abu Dhabiâ€™s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  decreased
0.2 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Arabtec Holding Co. (ARTC)   slumped 5.8 percent to 2.78
dirhams, the lowest close since March 27. Aabar Investments PJSC
and its units have acquired a 53 percent stake in the biggest
builder in the United Arab Emirates, Alrroya reported. Aabar
declined to comment when contacted by Bloomberg news. Officials
at Arabtec were not immediately available for comment.  National Investments Co. (NINV)   gained the most since
May 2, rising 1.4 percent to 148 fils. The  investment company 
posted a first-quarter profit of 2.9 million dinars ($10.4
million) after a loss of 1 million dinars in the year earlier
